05/04/2004
BUCHAREST, Romania -- The ruling Social Democratic Party (PSD) maintains the highest rating among political powers in the country, according to a new poll conducted by the CURS agency at the end of March.
Asked whom they would vote for if elections were held that day, 42 per cent chose the PSD.
The opposition National Liberal Party -- Democratic Party alliance came in second with 29 per cent.
Prime Minister Adrian Nastase remains the most popular politician.
(Rompres, Ziua - 05/04/04)
